**Lane Chosen:** Refresh / Content Opportunity Scoring

## Why I chose it

The goal of this project is to identify which content pages should be reviewed first for refresh or improvement. Websites often contain hundreds or thousands of pages, making it impossible to manually inspect every page. A data-driven ranking can help prioritize pages that are most likely to benefit from review.

I chose this lane because it focuses on supporting business decisions rather than simply training a machine learning model. The available dataset already contains search visibility, engagement, freshness, and content metrics that can help estimate which pages deserve attention first.],
   "source": ""
